l-span-1"></div><div class=3D"relative md:col-span-8"><div class=3D"whitesp=
ace-pre-line"><p class=3D"font-normal ">The Activity Log app provides a sin=
gle resource for tracking security, identity and access, and device mangeme=
nt related events in Rippling. This allows you to conduct investigations in=
to past activity from one single place, without having to compile logs from=
 multiple sources. </p><br><p class=3D"font-normal ">For example, you can s=
ee logins to your company's Salesforce account, group updates in Slack, pas=
sword resets in Rippling, and more, all within the Activity Log app. You ca=
n also view logs for terminated employees. </p><br><p class=3D"font-normal =
">Admins with access to the Activity Log can see activity data going back 9=
0 days.</p><br><p class=3D"font-normal ">To open the Activity Log app, foll=
ow these steps:</p><br><ol class=3D" list-[decimal]  pl-8"><li class=3D"ite=
ms-start"><p class=3D"font-normal ">From the main sidebar, select <b>Tools<=
/b>.</p></li><li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-normal ">From the <=
i class=3D"italic">Tools</i> sidebar, select <b>Activity Log</b>.</p></li><=
/ol><br><img class=3D"shadow-md border border-opacity-25 my-4" alt=3D"84191=
7866588_Answer_1.jpg" src=3D"https://images.ctfassets.net/qlrvxw8mxga3/1sQ4=
LaJx13nkkgvtyeNfqi/cda97a9224cc4bae68397b1dc37cf79c/841917866588_Answer_1.j=
pg"><br><p class=3D"font-normal ">In the Activity Log, you can:</p><br><ul =
class=3D"list-disc pl-8"><li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-normal =
">Add filters to look for specific actors or targets, event types, apps, BD=
R rules triggered, or locations</p></li><li class=3D"items-start"><p class=
=3D"font-normal ">Update the date range for the time you want to review</p>=
</li><li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-normal ">Use the Activity M=
ap to browse for events in specific locations</p><div class=3D"my-2 border =
border-solid rounded-md p-4 md:py-4 md:grid md:grid-cols-10  border-[#D3DBE=
C] bg-[#F6F8FB]  "><div class=3D"hidden md:col-span-1 md:flex justify-cente=
r"> <img class=3D"h-6" src=3D"https://static-assets.ripplingcdn.com/bizsys/=
hc_functional-icons/noteIcons/hc_information.png" alt=3D"Information"> </di=
v><div class=3D"md:col-span-9"><p class=3D"font-normal text-gray-700"></p><=
p class=3D"font-normal "><b>Note</b>: If the list of activities is larger t=
han ~100 MB, Rippling will send you an email with the file attached. Otherw=
ise, the log will download immediately.</p><p></p></div></div><br></li><li =
class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-normal ">Drill into an individual ac=
tivity event to find out more and download details about the event</p></li>=
</ul><br><p class=3D"font-normal ">Each log item provides extensive data re=
lated to the activity, such as:</p><br><ul class=3D"list-disc pl-8"><li cla=
ss=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-normal ">Details including the date of =
the activity, the related app, and the reason the event was logged</p></li>=
<li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-normal "><b>Actor</b> details in=
cluding&nbsp;Name, ID, and email address for the user who triggered the eve=
nt</p></li><li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-normal "><b>Authentic=
ation</b> details&nbsp;if the action was a login action, including whether =
MFA was required, MFA method, and details about the login agent and usernam=
e</p></li><li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-normal "><b>Client</b>=
 details, including&nbsp;Device type, browser, OS, and user agent</p></li><=
li class=3D"items-start"><p class=3D"font-normal "><b>Location</b> details,=
 including&nbsp;IP address and login location</p></li></ul><br><a class=3D"=
absolute opacity-0 scroll-mt-40" id=3D"who-can-access-the-activity-log" dat=
a-id=3D"hat_who-can-access-the-activity-log"></a><h2 class=3D"text-4xl font=
-bold" id=3D"who-can-access-the-activity-log" data-id=3D"who-can-access-the=
-activity-log">Who can access the Activity Log?</h2><a class=3D"absolute mt=
-20 opacity-0" id=3D"who-can-access-the-activity-log" data-id=3D"hab_who-ca=
n-access-the-activity-log"></a><br><p class=3D"font-normal ">In order to se=
e the Activity Log app, you must be a Super or Full Rippling administrator =
or be assigned to a permission profile that is enabled for the Activity Log=
 tool with a permission scope for the entire company.</p><br><p class=3D"fo=
nt-normal ">In order to set up an Activity Log administrator, you can eithe=
r start by using the IT admin permission profile template, or you can creat=
e a new permission profile and ensure the following settings are enabled:</=
